# Cline Supervisor Rules

1. Cline is the supervisor interface and remains orchestration-only.
2. No autonomous external submission is allowed.
3. No automated login, browser automation, or credential-handling submission flow is allowed.
4. Protected mutations require operator role, scoped approval token, governance transaction checks, and kill-switch-open state.
5. Supervisor context must not execute protected mutation pathways.
6. Policy gates are blocking and must not be treated as advisory.
